<p>Hello there!</p>
<p>Name's tordzak. I am a Spanish grad student in the UK. I have been following the site for around 4 years and I had the feeling of somehow contribute to the amazing SCP narrative.</p>
<p>I do not have a clear path to follow, but I would like to participate either by giving feedback to new content or providing new entries. I have been deeply moved by some of the SCP stories and I would be satisfied to do my part and pay homage to some of their ideas and concepts.</p>
<p>As for interests/hobbies; history and cartography, cinema and board games, gaming, horror and hard science fiction - whenever I disconnect from working in my thesis.</p>
<p>Some random thoughts that keep me up at night are quite involved with some SCPs. The hugest one is the dread of death: the feeling of nothingness and disappearance in the void, the meaninglessness of our daily routines; and how lying in bed and closing your eyes feels so close to that. I also think about pink elephants.</p>
<p>Thank you everyone for all the work you have done in this site!</p>

