<p><em>Do you remember, the twenty-first night of September…</em> oh wait wrong month.</p>
<p>Hello everyone! My name is Morgane, I am 25 years old, I live in France.</p>
<p>I first came across the SCP Foundation wiki three or four years ago, I think. I don't remember how I arrived here (I often find things through clicking on links at half-random, following the flow of my mind.) I joined the French branch in 2017 but didn't do anything there, save from opening a (quite empty) Sandbox.</p>
<p>I have regained interest in the SCP Foundation wiki quite recently, and I thought I may enjoy giving a comment or two, or maybe even trying to write one idea I have for a SCP article (if I ever have the energy to do so), so I decided to join the main site.</p>
<p>I currently have no hobbies due to depression problems, but once I feel better, I intend to pursue my former hobbies: doodling, learning to play the piano, composing music, imagining a fictional language and a fictional country… Something I still keep doing, however, is reading webcomics.</p>
<p>Things that keep me up at night? Loneliness, trauma, and the aforementioned depression. To ignore them, I spend a lot of time on the internet, resulting in short nights. Ha!</p>
<p>I am happy to join this corner of the Internet.</p>

							</div>

								
