<p>How is everyone doing?</p>
<p>My name is Joel.</p>
<p>Anyways, why am I here? Well, you can probably thank the Youtube video blogger Ekhert's Ladder for that. I was watching one of his videos, and found myself here, obsessively reading entries. Some have been better than others, but there have been others that have been inspiring, creative, and even downright iconic (SCP-682, what I call The Plot Armor Reptile, SCP-1342, or what I call: What NOT to do to your Closest, Possibly Only Ally, SCP-1000 Bigfoot, SCP-2273, or what I call YOU MANIACS and YOU BLEW IT UP!!!, etc.).</p>
<p>As someone who loves themes that explores extraterrestrial life, alternate universe, running gags (again, SCP-682), and more emotional themes, such as hope and fear, and cruelty and morality (Foundation seems to be somewhat lacking in far the latter, and has ample amounts of in the one before that), the SCP multiverse is a fascinating medium for exploring such concepts. And yes, I'm a huge nerd, who will without hesitation make TV culture references.</p>
<p>I hope to write one or two entries, since it isn't like I don't have at least one idea for an SCP. As for whether or not I actually complete it is another matter, since I have hobbies in drawing/Photoshop/Illustrator, and more than occasionally in video games, and hope to go back to school, and begin a major Political Science next season. Not to mention I'd need to stop reading entries long enough to write something of substance!</p>
<p>Don't expect me to write any stories of gore and dark creatures in darkened hallways here to steal the souls of any Mobile Task Forces foolish enough to try to capture him, and disembowel any researcher foolish enough to refer to him by &quot;it&quot; or &quot;SCP&quot; though. Do expect content like an alternate instance of SCP-682 getting a cameo, and being dragged out, kicking, screaming, and shouting threats to something that doesn't consider it welcome. Because that is my sense of humor.</p>
<p>The only thing that seems to keep me up at night is on nights where I know that I have to get up early in the morning, but my brain won't SHUT DOWN ALREADY! Oddly enough, knowing that my part time job isn't enough to afford to move out, and that it will take at least two years to do something about it does not keep me up, even though it probably should.</p>

							</div>

								
					
