<p>Hi there!</p>
<p>My name is Atlas (they/them), though I'll respond to pretty much anything. I got into SCP pretty recently thanks to a friend who writes stuff around here. I've been browsing the wiki pretty much constantly for the past two or so weeks. I'm not really sure I'll do much here besides lurk, but that might change at some point in the future. Who knows?</p>
<p>I spend most of my time playing video games and acting as a father to my two rat sons and my dog daughter. My other interests include MGS, fighting games, and music history. I also still have a plethora of German trivia carved into my brain from the four years I spent in German classes during high school.</p>
<p>Every night, I'm kept awake by a plague of self-doubt and fear that I will never amount to anything or achieve any goal I may set for myself in life. What if every dream and aspiration I've ever had has been perfectly achievable and the only thing keeping me from succeeding is myself? What if I do achieve the goal I think I want, only to realize that I only pursued it because it was easy, and my real goal is so much higher? What if I die before I figure out what I truly want in life?</p>
<p>Anyway, I'm very excited to finally be here and maybe put my overactive anxiety brain to use!</p>

